CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 13, 1957, pg. A12, reads: "Prize Winners - Recently, Tent no. 1 of the American Woodmen sponsored a baby contest at the Ebenezer Church Center. Mrs. Beatrice M. Mahaffey is the Worthy Guardian of the Tent, and Miss Johnnie Mae Jackson is the Commander. Mrs. Nellie Isenhour, chairman of the Tent's advisory board, served as the chairman of the contest, which was a great success. Here, Mrs. Isenhour stands with first-prize winner, Willie Pringle; Mrs. Gladys Smith, Mrs. Tucker, second-prize. Anya Michele Tucker; third-prize winner, Sheila Baynes, and Linda Durr."
TitMainTitle: Nellie Isenhour holding trophy with Gladys Smith holding Willie Pringle, Mrs. Tucker holding Anya Michele Tucker, and Sheila Baynes and Linda Durr standing in front, at baby contest sponsored by American Woodmen at Ebenezer Baptist Church
